#: src/unsafe-deep-dive/pinning/pin-and-drop.md
msgid ""
"Pinned types make guarantees about memory stability. Operations like `ptr::"
"read` and `mem::replace` can silently break these guarantees by moving or "
"duplicating data, invalidating internal pointers without the type system's "
"knowledge."
